description:
The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the Fidelity U.S. Momentum Factor Index℠.
 The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the Fidelity U.S. Momentum Factor Index℠, which is designed to reflect the performance of stocks of large and mid-capitalization U.S. companies that exhibit positive momentum signals. It may lend securities to earn income for the fund.
